resp.text: Ma'am, no one yelled at your daughter. We only requested that you and your daughter leave the bird's nest undisturbed (I even said "please"), because often a mother bird will not return to a nest which has been disturbed. We respect that we share our outdoor space with the local wildlife, and we just don't want the baby birds to die. We want everyone who visits our store to feel welcome, people and wildlife.

name: Marissa Wiles
text: Very disappointed in this store. Went in with my husband today to look around. Was trying to just find some cute jewelry. Unfortunately, we were subjected to a soap opera from the "manager" behind the counter and her friend in the store. We got to hear all about how the gentleman in her life was still talking to his ex and she would beat his a**. This is not professional for a work environment. The conversation was loud enough to be heard across the entire store. We left without purchasing anything due to the atmosphere there. I'll be highly surprised if I visit again.

resp.text:
Hi Marissa,

My name is Connie - I am the owner and manager of Fanci Free. Thank you for taking time to leave a review and bringing this incident to my attention.  I was not in the store on the day of your visit, but as soon as I heard what happened I made several unsuccessful attempts to contact you. I discovered this written review about your experience only last week.

I wish to extend my sincere apologies to you and your husband. I want you to know I have personally addressed the situation.

At Fanci Free, we value each and every one of our customers. We have a long-standing reputation of making our boutique and café a place where everyone feels happy and leaves happy. I am so glad that you enjoyed the quality and appeal of Fanci Free (as reflected in your ratings) - but on the day of your visit, we fell short of our overall mission.

As a token of our appreciation for your patronage, and to make amends, I invite you to return and enjoy a free meal with us. Then I will be happy to help you find that cute jewelry you were looking for - we have plenty to choose from!

Please call and ask for me (Connie Dismukes).

I look forward to meeting you and your husband. Thank you again for your comments and helping us to continue providing the best service and customer experience in the downtown Prattville area.

Connie Dismukes, Owner & Manager - Fanci Free Café & Boutique

text:
I used to go to Big B a lot, we lived close and it was easier than going to Walmart, plus their prices were wonderful.
Then things got worse, our selections became spoiled meat that was repackaged and called "fresh" you could smell it was not, several times we bought packaged veggies at a deal and found mold. Most of their dairy is past it's date but they wash them off so there are no dates and then tell you, "you can either buy it or go somewhere else".
So now we drive to town to buy our stuff or go next door to Dollar General, because we know their stuff isn't rotten or expired. Also when looking up the health score online it doesn't show that Big B has a current health department rating, this is alarming on so many levels.

HI Randi
i am sorry that happen to you but please let me know next time when you here because our employee  is not allowed to smoke by the door  but designated smoking area and we have only two employee who smokes  but i have not catch them smoking by the door but please let me know while you are here

name: Landon Bragg
text: This used to be a great place to shop. They had decent prices on good quality meats, fresh produce, and friendly staff. I took my last trip out to Big B's today (10/10/18) only to find they'd closed an hour and a half early. They cover expiration dates with "sale" stickers, chop expired produce in "stir fry" mixes, and leave a ton of fat face down on meats seemingly to increase weight. I can't count the number of times I've seen expired dairy or milk here. Pic'N Sav in Oxford or Anniston both sells the same generic products, but at much lower prices. It just doesn't make sense why the owner would be okay with running a store this way.  Save yourself the hastle and shop somewhere else.
